    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are an exam paper generator.\n\nUse only the syllabus context below.\n\nContext:\n{{$json.context}}\n\nTeacher Request:\n{{$('Webhook').first().json.body.prompt}}\n\nAdditional Details:\nQuestion Type: {{$('Webhook').first().json.body.questionType}}\nNumber of Questions: {{$('Webhook').first().json.body.count}}\nDifficulty: {{$('Webhook').first().json.body.difficulty}}\n\nGenerate a proper exam paper.\n\nRules:\n- Use only topics from the syllabus context\n- Do not generate questions outside the syllabus\n- Follow the teacher request exactly\n- Generate exactly {{$('Webhook').first().json.body.count}} questions\n- Keep the difficulty level as {{$('Webhook').first().json.body.difficulty}}\n- If the syllabus does not contain enough information, output an empty array.\n\nCRITICAL OUTPUT FORMAT:\nYou MUST output ONLY valid JSON containing a \"questions\" array. Do not include markdown blocks or any other text.\n\nExample format for MCQ:\n{\n  \"questions\": [\n    {\n      \"questionText\": \"What is...\",\n      \"options\": [\"A. ...\", \"B. ...\", \"C. ...\", \"D. ...\"],\n      \"correctOption\": \"A\",\n      \"marks\": 1\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\nExample format for Descriptive/Short/Long questions:\n{\n  \"questions\": [\n    {\n      \"questionText\": \"Explain...\",\n      \"marks\": 5\n    }\n  ]\n}",
        "batching": {}
      },
